author: Bob Davis
title: No Progress Seen in China-U.S. Economic Talks
text:
WASHINGTON—China’s top economic envoy made no visible progress in restarting negotiations with the U.S. after two days of meetings here, said individuals briefed on the talks.
Liu He, a close ally of Chinese President Xi Jinping who is slated to be named vice premier, met with a trio of senior Trump administration officials on Thursday and Friday, looking to find out what specifically the U.S. sought from China and to relaunch negotiations over opening the Chinese market.
